20% of your pages have redirects (3xx).

Although page redirects are basically designed to facilitate user experience, using too many of them may negatively affect your site's UX. Moreover, you may put your site in danger of falling out of Google's favor, as it may consider your website to be poorly maintained. To prevent your SEO from being negatively impacted, keep an eye on your temporary redirects and make sure that all of them are justified. If they're not, don't hesitate to eliminate them.
